# Tailwind CSS v4 — Key Changes

This project uses **Tailwind CSS v4**. Do NOT use v3 patterns. Follow these rules precisely.

---

## Installation & Setup

**No `tailwind.config.js` file.** Configuration lives in CSS.

**PostCSS setup:**
```js
// postcss.config.js
export default { plugins: ["@tailwindcss/postcss"] };
```

**Vite setup (preferred):**
```ts
// vite.config.ts
import tailwindcss from "@tailwindcss/vite";
export default defineConfig({ plugins: [tailwindcss()] });
```

**CSS entry point — one line only:**
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```
❌ Never use `@tailwind base`, `@tailwind components`, `@tailwind utilities` — those are v3.

---

## Configuration: CSS-First (`@theme`)

All design tokens are defined in CSS using `@theme`, not in a JS config file.

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --font-display: "Satoshi", sans-serif;
  --breakpoint-3xl: 1920px;
  --color-brand-500: oklch(0.72 0.19 142);
  --ease-fluid: cubic-bezier(0.3, 0, 0, 1);
}
```

These automatically become CSS custom properties on `:root` and power all utilities.

---

## Content Detection

❌ Do NOT configure a `content` array — it no longer exists.

v4 automatically detects template files. To add a source manually:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@source "../node_modules/@my-company/ui-lib";
```

---

## Dynamic Utility Values

Many utilities now accept **any value** without arbitrary value syntax:

```html
<!-- ✅ v4: any number works out of the box -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-15 w-17 mt-29"></div>

<!-- ❌ v3 style arbitrary values no longer needed for these -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-[15] w-[4.25rem]"></div>
```

Spacing is derived from a single `--spacing` variable: `mt-8` → `calc(var(--spacing) * 8)`.

---

## Gradients

`bg-gradient-*` is **renamed** to `bg-linear-*`.

```html
<!-- ✅ v4 -->
<div class="bg-linear-to-r from-indigo-500 to-pink-500"></div>
<div class="bg-linear-45 from-blue-500 to-teal-400"></div>

<!-- ❌ v3 — do not use -->
<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 to-pink-500"></div>
```

New gradient types:
```html
<div class="bg-radial-[at_25%_25%] from-white to-zinc-900 to-75%"></div>
<div class="bg-conic/[in_hsl_longer_hue] from-red-600 to-red-600"></div>
```

Interpolation modifiers: `bg-linear-to-r/oklch`, `bg-linear-to-r/srgb`, etc.

---

## Container Queries (Built-in)

❌ Do NOT install `@tailwindcss/container-queries` — it's in core now.

```html
<div class="@container">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 @sm:grid-cols-3 @lg:grid-cols-4"></div>
</div>
```

Max-width container queries:
```html
<div class="grid grid-cols-3 @max-md:grid-cols-1"></div>
```

Range queries:
```html
<div class="flex @min-md:@max-xl:hidden"></div>
```

---

## New Variants

### `not-*`
```html
<div class="not-hover:opacity-75"></div>
<div class="not-supports-hanging-punctuation:px-4"></div>
```

### `starting` (@starting-style — enter/exit transitions, no JS)
```html
<div popover class="transition-discrete starting:open:opacity-0 ..."></div>
```

### `inert`
```html
<div inert class="inert:opacity-50"></div>
```

### `in-*` (implicit group, no `group` class needed)
```html
<div class="in-hover:underline"></div>
```

### `nth-*`
```html
<li class="nth-2:font-bold"></li>
```

### `descendant`
```html
<div class="descendant:text-sm"></div>
```

---

## 3D Transform Utilities (New)

```html
<div class="perspective-distant">
  <article class="rotate-x-51 rotate-z-43 transform-3d"></article>
</div>
```

New utilities: `rotate-x-*`, `rotate-y-*`, `scale-z-*`, `translate-z-*`, `perspective-*`, `transform-3d`.

---

## New Utility Classes

| Utility | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `inset-shadow-*` | Inset box shadow (stack up to 4 layers) |
| `inset-ring-*` | Inset ring shadow |
| `field-sizing-content` | Auto-resize textarea without JS |
| `color-scheme-dark` / `color-scheme-light` | Fix scrollbar color in dark mode |
| `font-stretch-*` | Variable font width control |

---

## Color Palette

Colors are now `oklch`-based (P3 wide gamut) instead of `rgb`. Values are more vivid. The naming scale (`-100` through `-900`) is the same, but exact color values have changed.

Colors are accessible as CSS variables: `var(--color-blue-500)`, `var(--color-red-300)`, etc.

---

## Built-in `@import` Bundling

❌ Do NOT add `postcss-import` — v4 handles CSS `@import` bundling natively.

```js
// ❌ v3 postcss.config.js — do not copy this
export default { plugins: ["postcss-import", "@tailwindcss/postcss"] };

// ✅ v4
export default { plugins: ["@tailwindcss/postcss"] };
```

---

## Custom Data Attributes (No Config Needed)

```html
<!-- ✅ Just use the attribute directly -->
<div data-current class="opacity-75 data-current:opacity-100"></div>
```

No need to extend `tailwind.config.js` with `matchVariant` or custom variants for basic boolean data attributes.
